data.title: FELTON GROVE
data.meta_description: Posts about Timeline written by vickiwees
data.text:
Includes significant events in and around Felton Grove: Oct. 1875: Opening of Santa Cruz and Felton Railroad (old Felton station) and San Lorenzo Flume. Oct. 1876: A large party at Hager’s Grove (almost certainly Felton Grove, leased from Charles McLaughlin). … Continue reading →

July 1873: Independence Day celebrated at picnic ground across river (Felton Grove), featuring new dance floor. May 1875: George Treat’s $30,000 mortgage on Zayante Rancho foreclosed by Charles McLaughlin. July 1875: Campers from Santa Cruz at grove across river. July … Continue reading →
